item.title: help
item.dc:creator: lexa2
item.description:
You could:
a) Stop expecting to get useful advice in a second after the post.
b) Stop expecting to get useful advice if you do not read “BEFORE YOU POST” sticky and follow the reporting guidelines posted there.
c) Stop expecting to get any help in forum section dedicated for bug-reporting while there’s a separate “HELP!” forum section.

Providing details on the problem (what happened? when? what are you been doing at that moment? what hard you done then? had the problem persist?) are crucial for people on forum to be able to help you.
Providing details on your system specs (hardware/software) is a must if you want people to help you troubleshoot hardware/software-related problem.
